{
  "texts": [
    "Various studies have already investigated the more general translation abilities of GPT models.",
    "Among those are the work by Hendy et al. (2023); Jiao et al. (2023) and Wang et al. (2023) which evaluates GPT models for MT on a sentence-level (Hendy et al., 2023; Jiao et al., 2023; Wang et al., 2023) and on a document-level Hendy et al. (2023); Wang et al. (2023).",
    "Hendy et al. (2023) conducted an extensive automatic and human evaluation.",
    "They assessed the performance of three GPT models (ChatGPT, GPT3.5 (text-davinci-003), and text-davinci002) on 18 language pairs across 4 domains and compared it to state-of-the-art (research and commercial) translation systems.",
    "They used the top-ranked systems from the WMT evaluation campaign to identify the state-of-theart and the respective baselines for comparison."
  ]
}